## Cross-model review (codex) — pattern
```bash
codex exec -s danger-full-access --skip-git-repo-check -c model_reasoning_effort=high -C "<dir>" "<prompt>" < /dev/null 2>&1 | tee ai/tasks/<id>/codex-<stage>-run.log
```
Run it **in the background** (`run_in_background`); `< /dev/null` so it doesn't hang on open stdin. After the run:
**failure-scan** the log FIRST (usage / rate-limit — a 5-hour limit; harmless noise like `ConstrainedLanguage`)
→ then read the verdict `VERDICT: APPROVE` / `NEEDS REVISION` at the end. **Verify each finding against the code**,
write `audit-iterN.md`, repeat until APPROVE. Discipline — `skills/orchestrator-verify`, `docs/methodology/`.

## taskctl lifecycle (tracker = **{{TRACKER}}**, project **`{{JIRA_KEY}}`**)
`taskctl.config.json` sets `tracker={{TRACKER}}`. `taskctl` = `node taskctl/cli.mjs` (from this repo's root).
```bash
node taskctl/cli.mjs new <slug>            # local task -> ai/tasks/<id>/context.md + state.json
node taskctl/cli.mjs do plan <id>          # planner(claude) writes plan.md -> read it
node taskctl/cli.mjs do plan-review <id>   # reviewer(codex) reviews -> you VERIFY findings -> revise -> APPROVE
node taskctl/cli.mjs do run <id>           # implementation in a per-task git worktree (from origin/{{INTEGRATION_BRANCH}})
node taskctl/cli.mjs do review <id>        # cross-model code-review of the diff -> audit -> fix-loop -> APPROVE
node taskctl/cli.mjs status [<id>]
```
- `plan.md` must contain the line **`Verdict: APPROVE`** before `run`.
- `publish` / `autopilot` require a working {{TRACKER}} tracker; the PR into protected `{{PR_TARGET}}` is a feature-branch → PR with the user's explicit OK.
